org.apache.river.outrigger.snaplogstore

Class BaseObject<T extends StorableObject<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.river.outrigger.snaplogstore.BaseObject<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, StoredObject<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Resource

    class BaseObject<T extends StorableObject<T>>
extends Object
implements StoredObject<T>, Serializable
    Top level wrapper class for persisting outrigger objects. The target object is serialized and stored here as a byte array.

      • restore

        public T restore(T object)
          throws IOException,
                 ClassNotFoundException
        Description copied from interface: StoredObject
        Restore the state of a StorableObject object. There are two use cases for this method:
        1. The object passed in is restored with the stored state and the same object returned.
        2. The object passed in is immutable and a copy with the restored state is returned.
        Specified by:
        restore in interface StoredObject<T extends StorableObject<T>>
        Parameters:
        object - to restore
        Returns:
        a restored instance of T
        Throws:

        ClassNotFoundException - if class not found.
